      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tagName": "p",
        "properties": {},
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "At the same time, Chinese health workers in Wuhan and its broader Hubei Province — where some 60 million people are effectively quarantined — have struggled to deal with the sheer number of people who may have been infected. ",
            "position": {
              "start": {
                "line": 1805,
                "column": 112,
                "offset": 746279
              },
              "end": {
                "line": 1805,
                "column": 337,
                "offset": 746504
              }
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "element",
            "tagName": "a",
            "properties": {
              "href": "https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/02/world/asia/china-coronavirus-wuhan.html",
              "rel": [
                "noopener",
                "noreferrer"
              ]
            },
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "Hospitals are overwhelmed, and there aren’t enough testing kits",
                "position": {
                  "start": {
                    "line": 1805,
                    "column": 464,
                    "offset": 746631
                  },
                  "end": {
