              },
              "end": {
                "line": 1806,
                "column": 349,
                "offset": 747071
              }
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": " for more than a month as the virus spread.",
            "position": {
              "start": {
                "line": 1806,
                "column": 349,
                "offset": 747071
              },
              "end": {
                "line": 1806,
                "column": 392,
                "offset": 747114
              }
            }
          }
        ],
        "position": {
          "start": {
            "line": 1806,
            "column": 63,
            "offset": 746785
          },
          "end": {
            "line": 1806,
            "column": 396,
            "offset": 747118
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tagName": "p",
        "properties": {},
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "The outlet noted teams with the CDC’s Epidemic Intelligence Service can be ready to travel within 24 hours, but China’s ambassador to the Untied States, Cui Tiankai, wouldn’t say Sunday if the agency would be allowed to send experts to the country, at least as direct emissaries.",
            "position": {
              "start": {
                "line": 1807,
                "column": 66,
                "offset": 747190
              },
              "end": {
                "line": 1807,
                "column": 345,
                "offset": 747469
              }
            }
          }
        ],
        "position": {
          "start": {
            "line": 1807,
            "column": 63,
            "offset": 747187
          },
          "end": {
            "line": 1807,
            "column": 349,
            "offset": 747473
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tagName": "p",
        "properties": {},
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "“We welcome the American expert to participate in our efforts. And we are coordinating with the World Health Organization because a lot of things are done under the auspices of the [agency]. … American experts are on the list recommended by the W.H.O.,” ",
            "position": {
              "start": {
                "line": 1808,
                "column": 66,
                "offset": 747545
              },
              "end": {
                "line": 1808,
                "column": 320,
                "offset": 747799
              }
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "element",
            "tagName": "a",
            "properties": {
              "href": "https://www.cbsnews.com/news/transcript-cui-tiankai-on-face-the-nation-february-9-2020/",
              "rel": [
                "noopener",
                "noreferrer"
              ]
            },
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "Cui said during an interview",
                "position": {
                  "start": {
                    "line": 1808,
                    "column": 460,
                    "offset": 747939
                  },
                  "end": {
                    "line": 1808,
                    "column": 488,
                    "offset": 747967
                  }
                }
              }
            ],
            "position": {
              "start": {
                "line": 1808,
                "column": 320,
                "offset": 747799
              },
              "end": {
                "line": 1808,
                "column": 492,
                "offset": 747971
              }
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": " with CBS’ Face the Nation. “Even beyond that, some American experts have come to China already on their own individual basis.”",
            "position": {
              "start": {
                "line": 1808,
                "column": 492,
                "offset": 747971
              },
              "end": {
                "line": 1808,
                "column": 619,
                "offset": 748098
              }
            }
          }
        ],
        "position": {
          "start": {
            "line": 1808,
            "column": 63,
            "offset": 747542
          },
          "end": {
            "line": 1808,
            "column": 623,
            "offset": 748102
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tagName": "p",
        "properties": {},
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Cui continued to reject assertions that the Chinese government is working to silence those speaking out about the spread of the virus, including Li Wenliang, the doctor who was one of the first to raise concerns about the epidemic. ",
            "position": {
              "start": {
                "line": 1809,
                "column": 66,
                "offset": 748174
              },
              "end": {
                "line": 1809,
                "column": 298,
                "offset": 748406
              }
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "element",
            "tagName": "a",
            "properties": {
              "href": "https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/06/world/asia/chinese-doctor-Li-Wenliang-coronavirus.html",
              "rel": [
                "noopener",
                "noreferrer"
              ]
            },
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "Li died on Friday",
                "position": {
                  "start": {
                    "line": 1809,
                    "column": 440,
                    "offset": 748548
                  },
                  "end": {
                    "line": 1809,
                    "column": 457,
                    "offset": 748565
                  }
                }
              }
            ],
            "position": {
              "start": {
                "line": 1809,
                "column": 298,
                "offset": 748406
              },
              "end": {
                "line": 1809,
                "column": 461,
                "offset": 748569
              }
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": " after contracting the virus himself. Cui also lambasted unfounded claims from U.S. Sen. Tom Cotton (R-Ark.), who suggested the virus came from the country’s biological weapons program.",
            "position": {
              "start": {
                "line": 1809,
                "column": 461,
                "offset": 748569
              },
              "end": {
                "line": 1809,
                "column": 646,
                "offset": 748754
              }
            }
          }
        ],
        "position": {
          "start": {
            "line": 1809,
            "column": 63,
            "offset": 748171
          },
          "end": {
            "line": 1809,
            "column": 650,
            "offset": 748758
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tagName": "p",
        "properties": {},
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "“It’s very dangerous to stir up suspicion, rumors and spread them among the people,” the ambassador said. He continued to say he was saddened by Li’s death. “He was a devoted doctor, and he did his best to protect people’s health. We are so grateful to him. But you see, he was a doctor and a doctor could be alarmed by some individual cases.”",
            "position": {
              "start": {
                "line": 1812,
                "column": 66,
                "offset": 748832
              },
              "end": {
                "line": 1812,
                "column": 409,
